## Phase 3: Dynamic Testing (if HAS_URL)

Use URL from `$ARGUMENTS`. All commands use `curl` via bash.

### 3.1 Identity Headers (always run)

```bash
# These should return NO output:
curl -sI <url> | grep -iE "^(server|x-powered-by|x-generator|x-aspnet-version|x-runtime|via|x-drupal|x-wp-):"

# ETag format: hex-hex means nginx mtime leak
curl -sI <url> | grep -i "^etag:"

# Last-Modified leaks deployment time
curl -sI <url> | grep -i "^last-modified:"
```

`Server: nginx/1.18.0` → [HIGH] (version). `Server: nginx` → [LOW] (brand). `ETag: "abc-def"` → [LOW] (mtime).

### 3.2 Security Headers (always run)

```bash
curl -sI <url> | grep -iE "^(strict-transport-security|content-security-policy|x-frame-options|x-content-type-options|referrer-policy|permissions-policy):"
```

All six should be present. Flag each missing one as [MEDIUM].

### 3.3 SSL/TLS

```bash
echo | openssl s_client -connect <hostname>:443 2>/dev/null | grep -E "Protocol|Cipher"
```

TLS 1.0 or 1.1 → [HIGH]. Weak ciphers (RC4, DES, EXPORT) → [HIGH]. Expired cert → [CRITICAL].

### 3.4 Sensitive Paths

```bash
for path in /.git/config /.env /.env.local /backup.sql /config.php /.htaccess /admin /wp-login.php /phpinfo.php /_next/BUILD_ID /api/debug; do
  code=$(curl -so /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" <url>$path)
  [ "$code" != "404" ] && echo "[$code] $path"
done
```

`200` on `/.git/config` or `/.env` → [CRITICAL]. `200` on `/_next/BUILD_ID` → [LOW] (confirms Next.js, leaks build hash).

Also fetch `robots.txt` and read its content - a 200 is expected, but check if it discloses internal paths like `/admin`, `/api/`, or `/internal/`. Flag any sensitive path exposure as [LOW].

### 3.5 Framework Path Fingerprints

```bash
# Unobfuscated Next.js (should 404 if obfuscated)
curl -so /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" <url>/_next/static/
# Obfuscated path (should 200 if using _s/ convention)
curl -so /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" <url>/_s/static/

# Source maps
curl -so /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" <url>/_next/static/chunks/main.js.map

# Other frameworks
curl -so /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" <url>/wp-content/
curl -so /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" <url>/__nuxt/
```

`200` on unobfuscated `/_next/` → [LOW]. `200` on source map → [MEDIUM].

### 3.6 Port Exposure (if HAS_DB or HAS_NGINX)

```bash
for port in 3306 5432 6379 27017 9200 8080 8443; do
  nc -zw2 <hostname> $port 2>/dev/null && echo "OPEN: $port"
done
```

Any DB/cache port open to internet → [HIGH].

